'Cheyenne' ( or ) (Arapaho: HÃ­tesÃ­Ã­no'Ã³owÃº' {{cite web
| title = English-Arapaho dictionary accessdate = 2012-05-23 url =
| http://linguistics.berkeley.edu/~arapaho/english_arapaho.html
}} ) is the capital and most populous city of the US state of Wyoming and
the county seat of Laramie County. It is the principal city of the Cheyenne,
Wyoming, Metropolitan Statistical Area which encompasses all of Laramie County.
The population was 59,466 at the 2010 census.
Cheyenne is the northern terminus of the extensive and fast-growing Front Range
Urban Corridor. Cheyenne is situated on Crow Creek and Dry Creek. The Cheyenne,
Wyoming Metropolitan Area had a 2010 population of 91,738, making it the 354th
most populous metropolitan area in the United States.
